In order to upload a file using InputStreams and TransferManager something like this has to be done:

```java
ObjectMetadata objectMetadata = new ObjectMetadata();
objectMetadata.setContentLength(file.length());
TransferManager transferManager = TransferManagerBuilder.standard()
        .withS3Client(s3Instance())
        .withMinimumUploadPartSize(5 * 1024 * 1024) // min size for non-final multipart chunks is 5MB
        .withMultipartUploadThreshold(10 * 1024 * 1024) // set any threshold for multipart , using 10MB as example
        .build();

try (InputStream inputStream = new FileInputStream(file)) {
    Upload upload = transferManager.upload(bucketName, key, inputStream, objectMetadata);
    UploadResult uploadResult = upload.waitForUploadResult();
    // do more stuff...
}
```

Use try-with-resources in order to open and close the file input stream properly.

Also bear in mind that chunk size for non-final fragments of multipart uploads must be &gt;= 5MB in size (otherwise the aws API may reject the fragment).

ContentLength is recommended to be specified in the ObjectMetadata to upload InputStreams with TransferManager.

